cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SY, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multi-robot path planning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses a Linear Temporal Logic formula to specify the mission and an optimizing proposition. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses temporal logic to specify the mission and optimizing proposition. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper models the robots' motion as a weighted transition system and uses a timed automaton representation. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents an algorithm for optimizing the group motion.
